  "response": "No, Yo Yo Honey Singh did not attend the Indian Institute of Technology Bombay (IIT-B). Honey Singh, whose real name is Hirdesh Singh, is a prominent Indian music producer, singer, and rapper known for his work in the Punjabi and Hindi music industries. He gained fame through his catchy songs and energetic performances but does not have an academic background from IIT-B or any of the other Indian Institutes of Technology.\n\nIt's possible that misinformation or rumors may have circulated regarding his educational background, but there is no credible evidence to suggest that he was ever affiliated with IIT-B. Honey Singh's career has been primarily focused on music and entertainment rather than academics or engineering.\n\nIf you have any other questions or need further clarification, feel free to ask!",
